%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ddabeb8ea613c6a4e9bfb0c5a3d2dbb9, type: 3}
  m_Name: StillFailing
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueSequence
  lines:
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: 1984190853, guid: 1be9303cf68adf8469a107b28073a96a, type: 3}
    text: Still failing. The fans kicked on but the system shut itself down after
      a few seconds.
    showOnRightSide: 0
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: -2004239264, guid: f8402f94a4b63d44d90bf003f6ad06e0, type: 3}
    text: That's a classic failed POST, the motherboard is trying to start but something
      essential is still wrong
    showOnRightSide: 0
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: -2004239264, guid: f8402f94a4b63d44d90bf003f6ad06e0, type: 3}
    text: We remove one suspect component, try powering on again, and see if the
      problem changes.
    showOnRightSide: 0
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: -2004239264, guid: f8402f94a4b63d44d90bf003f6ad06e0, type: 3}
    text: We already pulled the GPU, so it's not that. Let's try the RAM next. Faulty
      memory is one of the most common causes of POST failure.
    showOnRightSide: 0
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: -2004239264, guid: f8402f94a4b63d44d90bf003f6ad06e0, type: 3}
    text: Go ahead, remove the RAM stick.
    showOnRightSide: 0
